Revision history for even-codex

0.29 2026-06-01

    - add a governed hybrid voice-query flow to the `D2-Codex` Even Hub app
      so a glasses click can open the popup, start a speech-recognition
      attempt in the companion webview, mirror recognised text into the draft,
      and submit through the existing action path
    - request the documented `g2-microphone` permission for the hybrid voice
      flow and expose explicit phone-side `Start Voice` and `Stop Voice`
      controls for proof and fallback handling
    - add a browser-level Playwright proof for `glasses click -> voice draft ->
      send` and refresh the governed release records around the new voice flow
    - align the popup state machine to the reviewed modal flow so an empty
      standby click closes cleanly and a recording click stops capture before
      deciding whether a recognised draft exists to submit
    - add a dedicated README end-to-end flow section so the shipped docs explain
      the full path from bridge startup and Codex transcript streaming through
      glasses popup interaction and query submission back into Codex
    - launch the packaged native Codex binary in the simulator xterm so the
      non-root desktop runtime no longer falls into the Node wrapper self-update
      branch that can try `npm install -g @openai/codex@latest`
    - require simulator-launcher and Codex-startup tickets to prove the exact
      `dashboard even-codex.simulator start` path after refreshing the
      installed skill copy, so future release gates cannot stop at repo-only or
      container-only startup proof
    - make the phone-side plugin auto-refresh treat bridge session payloads as
      authoritative so latest prompt, progress, and reply panels track the real
      session state and stale progress text does not linger
    - add a browser-level proof that the phone-side plugin updates those status
      panels automatically without a manual refresh click
    - replace the popup `Voice UNSUPPORTED` dead-end with a focused phone
      composer fallback so glasses click still leads into a usable phone mic or
      typing path when browser speech recognition is unavailable

0.28 2026-06-01

    - rebuild the glasses page as a transcript region plus a bottom popup
      prompt box so a glasses click no longer takes over the full screen
    - keep the Codex transcript visible behind the popup and dismiss the popup
      after `Cancel`, `Send`, or double-click close

0.27 2026-06-01

    - keep the glasses transcript visible when the user presses `Click`
      without any staged, drafted, or reusable query to act on
    - require a real actionable draft before the glasses input view opens,
      so the simulator no longer swaps into a useless `No staged query` view

0.26 2026-06-01

    - fix the Hub WebView `POST /prompt` path by adding the CORS preflight
      response and header contract required for manual glasses-button sends
    - add the governed manual simulator-button release slice for glasses-side
      send proof

0.25 2026-06-01

    - align the glasses input flow to the current Even simulator click model
      so the transcript stays visible by default, click opens the staged query
      input view, swipe cycles actions only inside that view, and double-click
      returns to the transcript surface
    - add governed ticket records and screenshot-reviewed simulator proof for
      the click, swipe, and double-click reactions

0.24 2026-05-31
    - replace the glasses-side multi-pane layout with a single full-screen
      transcript container so native Even swipe scrolling no longer swaps the
      display into a draft or action pane
    - keep staged query controls on the phone side and record that the
      current Even SDK docs do not document a native hold-to-dictate popup
    - refresh the governed docs and tickets around the simplified glasses
      interaction model

0.22 2026-05-31
    - treat simulator glasses events that only carry `eventSource: 1` as
      click-compatible focus input so the noVNC click control remains usable
      when the current Even simulator omits `eventType`
    - harden the live simulator control path around the inconsistent click
      payloads observed during screenshot-reviewed E2E checks

0.21 2026-05-31
    - treat simulator-delivered glasses `DOUBLE_CLICK_EVENT` as focus-or-
      restore interaction instead of shutting the page down, because the
      current Even simulator maps click input to event type `3`
    - keep the glasses click flow usable in noVNC while preserving the recent
      conversation focus and restore behavior
    - update the governed release notes and proof workflow around the
      simulator-specific event mapping

0.20 2026-05-31
    - keep the glasses page geometry stable during conversation focus mode so
      simulator click and double-click controls no longer blank the display
    - make focus mode swap the header and footer copy while preserving the
      recent-turn conversation detail content
    - re-prove the glasses focus and restore flow with fresh noVNC review

0.19 2026-05-31
    - turn a glasses click into a deterministic conversation zoom instead of a
      generic pane toggle so the Even simulator shows the recent Codex turns
      in a readable focus layout
    - keep the focused glasses layout valid by retaining a footer area instead
      of rebuilding the page with a zero-height container
    - prove the fixed click and double-click simulator controls with fresh
      screenshot review in the noVNC desktop

0.18 2026-05-31
    - route simulator-side prompt submission through a dedicated xterm
      relauncher that resumes the paired Codex session with the new prompt,
      avoiding the live post-turn composer submit failure
    - keep the simulator desktop on the caller uid and replace the visible
      Codex window deterministically for each staged query
    - prove the fixed simulator bridge path with fresh noVNC screenshots and
      update the governed release record

0.17 2026-05-31
    - drive the paired Codex xterm with `xdotool` before falling back to
      direct tty writes so live simulator submissions land in the visible TUI
      and complete the real end-to-end query loop
    - prove the year and month glasses queries, glasses zoom controls, and
      real plugin transcript updates through fresh noVNC screenshot review
    - document the current Even SDK input limitation audit for voice entry and
      keep the simulator screenshot review as a standing release gate

0.16 2026-05-31
    - add a real `/prompt` bridge route that writes staged Even-plugin queries
      into the paired Codex TUI session
    - surface assistant progress text and recent turn history so the glasses
      focus view can show both recent queries and replies
    - add a reusable local rule that keeps screenshot interpretation outside
      the Perl `.t` suite and requires fresh human or LLM review for
      simulator E2E acceptance

0.15 2026-05-31
    - add a staged query composer with slash normalization so `Slash ...`
      becomes `/...` before the simulator flow stages the next Codex query
    - make the glasses-side input flow accept simulator click gestures that
      surface as system events and keep `Send`, `Retry`, and `Cancel` visible
    - prove the release with fresh noVNC screenshots for `hi -> Hi`, staged
      query state, and glasses-side action cycling outside the Perl `.t` suite

0.12 2026-05-31
    - run the Dockerized simulator desktop as the caller's host uid and gid by
      default so the mounted `~/.codex` tree is not rewritten by `root`
    - keep the live visual acceptance gate outside the Perl `.t` suite and
      prove the release through fresh screenshots of the Codex xterm, plugin,
      and glasses transcript surfaces

0.11 2026-05-31
    - route the latest paired Codex prompt and reply through `/session` and
      into both the bridge-served plugin and the packaged `D2-Codex` app
    - make the Dockerized simulator desktop resume the paired session through
      the real bundled Codex CLI binary and prove a visible `hi -> Hi` turn
    - add background transcript refresh in the Even Hub app so the phone-side
      plugin and glasses view catch up automatically to live Codex turns

0.10 2026-05-31
    - install the `codex` CLI inside the Dockerized simulator desktop image
    - mount the host `~/.codex` directory into the simulator container so
      existing Codex auth and config can be reused
    - record Codex availability inside the simulator startup flow and verify
      the container contract through governed tests

0.09 2026-05-31
    - make `dashboard even-codex.simulator start` launch a Dockerized noVNC
      desktop based on `developer-dashboard:latest`
    - add skill-local Docker Compose and simulator image assets that start
      the DD environment, bridge chain, and Even simulator together
    - inject the active workspace pairing into the containerized simulator
      flow so port `15700` is enough to view and test `D2-Codex`

0.08 2026-05-31
    - add multi-connector profile storage to the `D2-Codex` Even plugin so
      the phone app can save and switch between different local DD connectors
    - add per-connector Codex session libraries with phone-side activation and
      removal controls
    - add glasses-side session switching for the active connector while
      keeping connector switching phone-only

0.07 2026-05-31
    - add `dashboard even-codex.e2e {start,stop}` as a one-command desktop
      orchestration flow for the DD bridge, local Hub app server, and Even
      simulator
    - support runtime pid and log tracking for the bridge and app server in
      the E2E launcher
    - document and verify the local desktop E2E flow in Docker

0.06 2026-05-31
    - add `dashboard even-codex.simulator {start,stop}` as a bash CLI for
      local Even Hub simulator process control
    - record pid and log files under the skill runtime area and support env
      overrides for simulator bin, app URL, automation port, and runtime paths
    - document and verify the local simulator control workflow in Docker

0.05 2026-05-31
    - add Even Hub listing metadata, greyscale icon and background assets,
      and governed submission content for `D2-Codex`
    - add a simulator-backed screenshot capture workflow for Hub submission
    - prove the richer manifest fields still pack into a valid `.ehpk`

0.04 2026-05-31
    - upgrade the `D2-Codex` Even Hub app from a packaging-valid starter into
      a user-friendly phone-side setup and status workflow
    - rebuild the glasses view into three readable containers with header
      refresh, detail cycling, and clearer exit guidance
    - document and verify the stronger Even plugin UX through governed Docker
      tests and release records

0.03 2026-05-31
    - add a real Even Hub `D2-Codex` package manifest with documented
      edition, version floor, entrypoint, and network permission structure
    - add a Vite and TypeScript based Even Hub SDK app that creates the
      startup glasses page, persists the bridge origin, and handles root
      double-click exit plus foreground lifecycle events
    - add reproducible `build:hub` and `pack:hub` workflows so the skill can
      build `dist/index.html` and package `dist/d2-codex.ehpk`

0.02 2026-05-31
    - add a runnable LAN bridge slice with workspace-to-Codex pairing through
      `dashboard even-codex.start add <codex-session-id>`
    - add `dashboard even-codex.start` to serve the Even connector on port
      `6789` by default with `/health`, `/bootstrap`, and `/plugin/`
    - bundle the first Even plugin web app inside the skill repo and verify it
      with Docker tests and Playwright

0.01 2026-05-31
    - bootstrap governed even-codex skill repository
    - add production software specification in SPEC.md
    - add minimal spec metadata module and Docker-verified tests
    - add explicit local-network deployment mode to the production specification
    - map the specification into phased SOW workstreams
    - add Even::Codex::Protocol as the first runtime contract module
